        "subject": "LU-18141 efalnd: don't check for NULL before free'ing",
        "message": "LU-18141 efalnd: don't check for NULL before free'ing\n\nThe common free'ing macros already check for NULL,\nso we don't need to explicitly check this beforehand.\n\nThe patch has been generated with the coccinelle script below.\n\n@@\nexpression E;\n@@\n- if (E != NULL)\n(\n  OBD_FREE_PTR(E);\n|\n  OBD_FREE(E, ...);\n|\n  LIBCFS_FREE(E, ...);\n|\n  CFS_FREE_PTR(E);\n|\n  CFS_FREE_PTR_ARRAY(E, ...);\n)\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Timothy Day <timday@amazon.com>\nChange-Id: I1778ff3300ad0caebdf396f7732d66d3801f92f5\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/63072\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nReviewed-by: Yonatan Nachum <ynachum@amazon.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
